value.def: A minute is one of the sixty parts that an hour is divided into. People often say 'a minute' or 'minutes' when they mean a short length of time.

example.ex: The pizza will then take about twenty minutes to cook...
example.tran: 然后比萨饼做出来大约要用20分钟的时间。

example.ex: Bye Mum, see you in a minute...
example.tran: 妈妈，一会儿见。

example.ex: Half a minute later she came in the front door...
example.tran: 半分钟之后，她就从前门进来了。

example.ex: Within minutes we realized our mistake.
example.tran: 没过多久，我们就意识到了自己的错误。

value.def: The minutes of a meeting are the written records of the things that are discussed or decided at it.

example.ex: He'd been reading the minutes of the last meeting.
example.tran: 他刚才一直在阅读上次会议的记录。

value.def: When someone minutes something that is discussed or decided at a meeting, they make a written record of it.

example.ex: You don't need to minute that.
example.tran: 你不必把那一点记入会议记录。

value.def: People often use expressions such as wait a minute or just a minute when they want to stop you doing or saying something.

example.ex: Wait a minute, folks, something is wrong here...
example.tran: 等一下，伙计们，这里有点不对劲。

example.ex: Hey, just a minute!
example.tran: 嗨，等一下！

value.def: If you say that something will or may happen at any minute or any minute now, you are emphasizing that it is likely to happen very soon.

example.ex: It looked as though it might rain at any minute...
example.tran: 看上去好像马上就要下雨了。

example.ex: He ought to be back any minute...
example.tran: 他应该随时都会回来。

example.ex: Any minute now, that phone is going to ring.
example.tran: 那部电话随时可能响。

value.def: If you say that you do not believe for a minute or for one minute that something is true, you are emphasizing that you do not believe that it is true.

example.ex: I don't believe for one minute she would have been scared...
example.tran: 我压根不认为她会有所畏惧。

example.ex: I don't believe him for a minute.
example.tran: 我一点也不相信他。

value.def: A last-minute action is one that is done at the latest time possible.

example.ex: She was doing some last-minute revision for her exams...
example.tran: 她在为考试进行最后的复习。

example.ex: The location has been changed at the last minute...
example.tran: 在最后一刻改变了地点。

example.ex: He will probably wait until the last minute.
example.tran: 他也许会等到最后一刻。

value.tran: 最后关头; 最后一刻

value.def: You use the expression the next minute or expressions such as 'one minute he was there, the next he was gone' to emphasize that something happens suddenly.

example.ex: The next minute my father came in...
example.tran: 接着我父亲突然进来了。

example.ex: Jobs are there one minute, gone the next.
example.tran: 工作机会稍纵即逝。

value.tran: 下一刻(强调事情发生得很突然)

value.def: If you say that something happens the minute something else happens, you are emphasizing that it happens immediately after the other thing.

example.ex: The minute you do this, you'll lose control...
example.tran: 你一旦做了这件事，就会失去控制。

example.ex: The minute that the war started, everybody was glued to the television.
example.tran: 战事一起，所有人都盯紧了电视报道。

value.def: If you say that something must be done this minute, you are emphasizing that it must be done immediately.

example.ex: I need to speak with her right this minute...
example.tran: 我现在就需要跟她谈谈。

example.ex: Anna, stop that. Sit down this minute.
example.tran: 安娜，住手。马上坐下。

value.def: If you say that something is minute, you mean that it is very small.

example.ex: Only a minute amount is needed...
example.tran: 只需要很少的一点点。

example.ex: The party was planned in the minutest detail.
example.tran: 晚会策划极为详细。

value.tran: 非常细小的;十分微小的

min 小 + ce → 弄小 → 切碎
mini 小 + ature 物 → 小东西 → 小型物
mini 小 + fy 使… → 使…缩小
mini 小 + m → 微量，小量
minim 微量，小量 + ize 使… → 使缩小到最少
mini 小 + skirt 裙子 → 超短裙
min 小 + or 表情况 → 较小的；较少的
min 小 + us 表名词，用于科学术语 → 变少 → 减去
minus 减去 + cule 小 → 一减再减 → 极小的
min 小 + ute → 微小的，细微的
min 小 + ut 用 + ia 某种病 → 小事件 → 琐事
